# Web Infrastructure Design

## Overview
This project, part of the ALX System Engineering & DevOps track, involves designing and explaining a simple web infrastructure for hosting a website accessible via `www.foobar.com`. The task focuses on understanding key components of a web stack, their roles, and potential issues like SPOF, downtime, and scalability.

## Task 0: Simple Web Stack
- **Objective**: Design a one-server web infrastructure using a LAMP stack (Nginx, application server, MySQL) for `www.foobar.com`, mapped to IP `8.8.8.8`.
- **Diagram**: The infrastructure diagram is available at:  
  ![Simple Web Stack](https://flic.kr/p/2rdek8Q)
- **Details**: See the file `0-simple_web_stack.md` for the diagram and explanations of components (server, domain name, DNS record, web server, application server, database, communication protocol) and issues (SPOF, downtime, scalability).

